cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper analyzes the convolutional layers of a pre-trained neural network for image classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also investigates the diversity of neurons' responses, which is related to the network's learning and generalization abilities, and can be relevant to machine learning (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a visualization method to illustrate the learned content of each neuron, which can be useful for interpretability and explainability of deep learning models, and is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
